        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme component \"Maintenance and Input Cost for Intercropping in Oilpalm\" launched under the \"National Mission on Edible Oil–Oil Palm\" scheme aims to increase the production of oil palm and reduce imports by providing financial assistance for maintenance and intercropping.",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme component &amp;quot;Maintenance and Input Cost for Intercropping in Oilpalm&amp;quot; launched under the &amp;quot;National Mission on Edible Oil–Oil Palm&amp;quot; scheme by the Department of Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Co-operation, Government of Gujarat. aims to promote the cultivation of oil palm, enhance domestic production, and reduce dependency on imports. The scheme provides assistance to farmers for maintenance and intercropping during the four-year gestation period of oil palm plantations, ensuring the timely provision of essential inputs such as seeds, fertilizers, crop protection materials, and other related resources.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n  - **First Year:** ₹10,500/-.  - **Second Year:** ₹10,500/-.  - **Third Year:** ₹10,500/-.  - **Fourth Year:** ₹10,500/-.\n<br>\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "",
        "detailedDescription": [
          {
            "type": "align_justify",
